sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K634004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: An active form of BBa_K634002 under the constitutive J23100 promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kenneth O. Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K634002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The 2 component system that responds to ethanol that activates transcription of pexaA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kenneth O. Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Each part contains a RBS but the part does not contain a promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K634000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: ExaD phosphorylates ExaE, which is a transcription factor acting upon PexaA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Eric Walters
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: De novo synthesis, codon optimized for E. coli. Original amino acid sequence taken from Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The synthesis included a Shine-Dalgarno-complimentary RBS 5' of the gene.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K634001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: exaE is a transcription factor that is activated by phosphorylation from exaD. It acts upon pexaA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kenneth O. Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: de novo synthesis original amino acid sequence from pseudomonas aeruginosa.
